{"id":31078,"title":"[Adolescents and young adults in situations of addiction].","abstract":"Adolescence is a period of major readjustments during which experimenting with psychoactive substances is common and can, in some cases, lead to the development of long-term addictive behaviour. Identifying young people with a particular vulnerability for the development of such behaviour and offering them adapted support is therefore an important part of the care provided to adolescents.","date":"2014-01-13","categories":"Chemically-Induced Disorders","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24409573","annotations":[{"name":"Substance dependence","weight":0.8006,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Substance_dependence"},{"name":"Behavior","weight":0.781524,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Behavior"},{"name":"Adolescence","weight":0.701843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adolescence"},{"name":"Youth","weight":0.602129,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Youth"},{"name":"Psychoactive drug","weight":0.432167,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychoactive_drug"},{"name":"Chemical substance","weight":0.341444,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemical_substance"},{"name":"Adaptation","weight":0.155758,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adaptation"},{"name":"Lead","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lead"},{"name":"Child development","weight":0.0365852,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Child_development"},{"name":"Major","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Major"},{"name":"Vulnerability","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vulnerability"}]}
